  <name>Browsey</name>
  <summary>Fast and minimalist file explorer</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      Browsey is a lightweight file explorer built with a Rust/Tauri backend and a
      Svelte frontend.
    </p>
    <p>
      It is designed for fast navigation in large folders while keeping familiar
      desktop file-management workflows.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>List and grid views with virtualized rendering</li>
      <li>Recursive search, duplicate scans, and archive extract/compress tools</li>
      <li>Clipboard operations, trash management, and properties/permissions editing</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
